    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to map the large-scale distribution of cold molecular gas in NGC5548 using CO(1-0) line observations in Band 3, which do not yet exist for this galaxy. We will also measure the kinematics and the total gas and dynamical masses. NGC 5548 is the Rosetta Stone for understanding the active galaxy/quasar phenomenon and a large ancillary database exists, except at sub-mm and mm wavelengths. The wealth of supporting data from X-ray through IR energies allow us to relate the distribution of the various stellar populations to the molecular gas distribution. The high-resolution, sensitive maps of the large-scale distribution of the cold gas that ALMA can deliver will provide a comprehensive view of the constituents of this galaxy, illuminating the inter-relationships between the gas, stars, and the central black hole. These data will also provide a much needed reference for the many studies of molecular gas in high-z quasars on the typical content and nature of the cold molecular gas that remain after bulge formation has ceased and after the main growth phase of the central black hole and how this gas is related to the distribution of stars of various ages in the galaxies.</prp:abstract>
